attributes.content: Gkhaa—!
attributes.name: Ink Spirit

attributes.content: Is it just me or there are fewer of them?
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: It does look that way, and they don't seem that scary any more.
attributes.name: Kroos

attributes.content: Could they have forgotten about us?
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: Day after day, year after year, all that they ever do is attack the village for naught... it's wretched, and heartwrenching!
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: How would you know? They don't talk—
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: They—I suppose they just might be able to speak.
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: What? The head priest always said we must forever be compassionate. If that really is the case, then we are in quite a pickle...
attributes.name: Saga

attributes.content: But if this is really just a painting...
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: Maybe we've already found the right place.
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: I should've figured this out sooner. Damn it, Nian... She didn't tell us about this on purpose...
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: She's probably worried we'd let something slip that would tip Dusk off and let her get away.
attributes.name: Kroos

attributes.content: Would someone that powerful even run? To be honest with you, I'm a little scared of her...
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: Let's not talk about how all of this works for now. She's keeping us live humans hostage in this little world she created for herself. What's this supposed to mean?
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: Anything we eat might as well be real, and not only that, the people here can actually hold a conversation. Is this supposed to mean anything?
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: If she's able to do all this with just Arts, then this sister of Nian's—
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: You're right about that... I've seen lots of weird Originium Arts before, but this is maybe a little too out there.
attributes.name: Kroos

attributes.content: My... Never in a thousand moons would I have imagined the person you are looking for could be so... extraordinary.
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: Is that so? Here I was thinking that, of all the places I've visited, this P'o-shan has to be one of the simplest, most unassuming towns.
attributes.name: Saga

attributes.content: Where have you been...?
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: Why, I could go all morning about this.
attributes.name: Saga

attributes.content: During my travels, I have come across many an odd character. I have met someone who would use ale as a blade and betake herself like lightning. I have also seen someone fight with the most peculiar style, able to swim up a waterfall.
attributes.name: Saga

attributes.content: I have met one so sagacious, he could write a poem in eight steps. Alas, he offended the wrong men, and practically had to bring with him his own coffin to his final audience with his liege.
attributes.name: Saga

attributes.content: I have seen the famed Boulder of Pei-Hsüan. According to legend, in eras past, the boulder sprang up from the ground, suspending in midair when an emperor of the past ascended to his throne.
attributes.name: Saga

attributes.content: At first, it was thought to portend the country's prosperous future under his rule, but it was also thought to mean he had a heavy load to bear, and was thus seen as an omen by many.
attributes.name: Saga

attributes.content: I have visited a mountain that scraped the skies, where, amidst the clusters of Originium left behind by Catastrophes, there stood solemnly a towering pine tree, reaching upwards, as though splitting the sea of clouds in twain.
attributes.name: Saga

attributes.content: I have seen many a blade piercing chessboards, books sauteed in woks. I have also met a woman of Yen performing the most extraordinary feat, forging a city all on her own. Yet, strangely, it was hazy in appearance, and she would only allow us to view the city from afar, not in its vicinity.
attributes.name: Saga

attributes.content: I would be remiss to forget the Yen emperor's close friend from faraway lands. He told the Lung of his journey to the west, and of the countless towns and cities his travels took him.
attributes.name: Saga

attributes.content: Each and every time he spoke, I could see the townscapes before my eyes!
attributes.name: Saga

attributes.content: —Anyway, I know a thing or two because I've seen a thing or two.
attributes.name: Saga

attributes.content: Uhh, I know of this Boulder of Pei-Hsüan. I was under the impression it was destroyed years ago during a Catastrophe?
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: Exactly the one. I saw it float with my own eyes—
attributes.name: Saga

attributes.content: How many years ago was that?!
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: I just want to make sure. The person you speak of... That's her sister?
attributes.name: Saga

attributes.content: That's right.
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: How is their relationship...?
attributes.name: Saga

attributes.content: Oh~ Getting right to the meat of it.
attributes.name: Kroos

attributes.content: Could it be the sisters are not on the best of terms?
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: Remember the thing I showed you? Nian gave me that. At first, I thought she gave it to us to prove our identities to Dusk...
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: Ohh, the fascinating little trinket? What is its purpose, then?
attributes.name: Saga

attributes.content: No idea...
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: Allow me? Oh, have you shown this to the storyteller?
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: Hm, has he seen it already? Did... Did he say anything about it?
attributes.name: Saga

attributes.content: He said he's never seen it.
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: I think... we should still have him take a look.
attributes.name: Saga

attributes.content: Err, if I may, there is actually one other thing that has left me quite perplexed...
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: What's up?
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: Well, I mean, my benefactor, you saw me take on one of the fiends, did you not?
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: Oh... You mean how it took you forever and a half just to get away from one of the Ink Spirits?
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: Precisely!
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: I saw it too, but why that all of a sudden?
attributes.name: Saga

attributes.content: Well... I am but a defenseless layman in the martial arts. Be that as it may, I cracked an entire canister of whoop-ass on the fiend. Surely you too must find that strange!
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: Uh... You call that a can of whoop-ass?
attributes.name: Kroos

attributes.content: —*Cough* *cough*! Umm, well, I have a few tricks up my sleeve—Now, I implore you, don't get the wrong idea. It's not that I don't want to do my part in our battle against the monsters. I just have my reasons—
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: So, your point is...?
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: Um, my benefactor, certainly you believe me?
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: I certainly believe you not. You may be good at tricking people, but definitely not me. If I couldn't figure this much out, I wouldn't be any use out here on a mission.
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: Oh, I had my doubts about that too! I saw Master Nothing dart away with the little girl on his back in no time and without a breaking a sweat. I am certain he is no less formidable than my fellow disciples back at the temple!
attributes.name: Saga

attributes.content: H-Haha, please, don't give me that look. I'm trying my best now, am I not?
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: Right! It's getting late! Let's make our way to the storyteller and check on him! He is ill, is he not?
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: *cough*... Are you here for my tales? My apologies, but I'm afraid I won't have any stories to tell today with the shape I'm in.
attributes.name: Storyteller

attributes.content: Please, you must get more rest. Just leave everything to us.
attributes.name: Villager

attributes.content: You need not worry. I'm fine... *cough*... This is the first time we've met, is it not? Where are you from, my friends?
attributes.name: Storyteller

attributes.content: Why, uh... I'm from quite far away. I'm merely passing through, but with all the men in the village singing the praises of your storytelling, I had to come hear for myself!
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: But if you're indisposed, then we could... pay you a visit another day. Yes, we shall return, haha.
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: A moment, please. *cough* I cannot fault you for not knowing, but we rarely have any visitors here in P'o-shan, and I am not one to turn away those who wish to hear my stories.
attributes.name: Storyteller

attributes.content: I have a guest room in my garden. Perhaps you would be so kind as to stay the night?
attributes.name: Storyteller

attributes.content: Are you feeling okay?
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: I'm not sure myself. It might just be a cold... though it certainly doesn't seem that way. The doctor wasn't sure of the cause either. I suppose it's a sign my body's gotten weaker because I've been neglecting my training. Please, don't pay it any mind.
attributes.name: Storyteller

attributes.content: I-Ch'uan, take them there.
attributes.name: Storyteller

attributes.content: Of course.
attributes.name: Villager

attributes.content: Well... We'll take you up on the offer, then.
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: Please, this way.
attributes.name: Villager

attributes.content: Why, this is peculiar. I walked out of this very house in the morning and went on a stroll, and now I'm being invited to stay here anew... This really makes no sense!
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: Well, my benefactors...
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: Nothing.
attributes.name: Kroos

attributes.content: Uh... Haha... *Ahem*. I am not getting out of this one, am I? I understand.
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: Well... Where should I begin...? After all, I've been deceiving the two of you right from the start.
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: That I've more or less figured out.
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: Please accept my apologies.
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: You sure know how to switch up your attitude quick, don't you? Oh well, whatever. I understand. You can't just completely trust a person you come across out in the wastes.
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: You have my thanks.
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: Are you from Kou-wu?
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: No... my hometown is farther north. Just your regular small town.
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: I had resigned myself to live a normal, uninteresting life as a plowboy. That summer, a few men from the cities came to our town, led by a fine, magnificent lady. She said I was the one they sought.
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: I was just thirteen at the time. They brought me to Kou-wu to a martial arts school, the Liens, and she was its master.
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: That's how I met my master, and all there was to it. I had room and board, and when I had the time, I could help out at construction sites and earn some coin to send to my family back home.
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: I remained diligent over the past ten years, but never once did I think my master did me a favor for taking me in.
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: I made it a point to rely on none but myself. I would rather go without a meal than be looked down upon by my master.
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: But... she was getting on in years. I once thought her formidable, matchless, even. But she was seriously ill. Couldn't even get a decent night's sleep.
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: That was when I came to realize I could stay there no longer. All my fellow disciples had left, and it was my time to do so as well.
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: But... last year, I killed someone by accident. Someone whom I should not have killed.
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: I thought it was a friendly match between dojos. It wasn't until much later that I found out the man had sold his life. He was meant to die by my hands.
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: The Lien style's reputation was already on its last legs, but they wanted to defame our name nonetheless. It was all a ploy to bring my master to swallow her pride and get her down on her knees.
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: —And then—
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: My master, her hair white as ash and braided just like my mother's, stood before all and spilled her own blood as the rules dictated!
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: ...My goodness!
attributes.name: Saga

attributes.content: 'Rules!' It's murder, I tell you!
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: I brought my unconscious master back, but they had our school completely surrounded.
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: I could not call for an ambulance, let alone my fellow disciples!
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: All I could do was watch her body turn cold. Their men stood outside, unmoving until they saw my poor master buried.
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: My master left me with this fan. I don't have the courage to use it, and certainly not the moves she taught me.
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: The school was lost, and I had no way to get in touch with my fellow disciples. So I concealed my identity, masquerading as a fortune teller, a Messenger.
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: But no matter the case, I did whatever it took to leave that city, and I will make my way to the capital or Lungmen, wherever. The more people there, the better—
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: —Then, one day, I shall return to Kou-wu City and make things right.
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: That is the story... my benefactor, Kroos, what you said on the day of the rescue. You had the right of it.
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: All those years I spent in Kou-wu City... I wasted.
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: I heard stories of the Yen martial artists' sense of honor, yet never would I have imagined such a tale...
attributes.name: Saga

attributes.content: So it wasn't just a traffic accident...
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: Correct... the villains had men in every corner of Kou-wu City! I watched in hiding from a nearby village, but luck was not on my side. In the end, my only choice was to find myself a car and skip town—
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: Your master had gone that far, and they still wouldn't leave you alone?
attributes.name: Kroos

attributes.content: Leave me alone?
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: If they had their minds set on leaving anyone alone, I doubt they would bend the rules to kill!
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: To think that there are rules this rotten and unreasonable... 'Twould seem there is yet much for me to learn about this world.
attributes.name: Saga

attributes.content: Alright then... This all sounds like something out of a martial arts novel, but well... I believe you.
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: *sobs*, my benefactor! Your reason moves me! As your stalwart underling, rest assured I'll do all that it takes to return the favor, come hell or high water!
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: *Sigh*...
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: My benefactor... you wouldn't think I'm still lying, would you?
attributes.name: Mr.Nothing

attributes.content: Well, you'd be one hell of a liar if that was a lie.
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: Please, come in.
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: *cough*... Full glad am I to find you here, my guests. I thought you would be resting in your room. Could you find our hospitality wanting, perchance...?
attributes.name: Storyteller

attributes.content: Uh, no, not at all. We are just talking about something among ourselves.
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: *cough*, I see... Pray accept my humblest apologies for interrupting. I merely wished to caution you against visiting Mt. Hung-tung. It is abound with monsters ahead of the New Year.
attributes.name: Storyteller

attributes.content: Okay, thanks for the reminder.
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: Most certainly. I shall take my leave now... *cough*—
attributes.name: Storyteller

attributes.content: Hope you get better soon.
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: What's up?
attributes.name: Kroos

attributes.content: The Umbrella-Boiler guy... You think he's from inside the painting?
attributes.name: Lava

attributes.content: If even this is part of the painting... what about us?
attributes.name: Lava
